WEBVTT

00:01.334 --> 00:03.378
- ♪ I GOT THE BEAT,
SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE WITH ME ♪

00:03.461 --> 00:05.046
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:05.130 --> 00:06.881
♪ PICK IT UP AND TURN AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:06.965 --> 00:08.550
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:08.633 --> 00:12.429
♪ ♪

00:12.512 --> 00:14.139
♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, HEY ♪

00:14.222 --> 00:16.056
- ♪ MIGHTY ♪
- ♪ LA, LA, WOW ♪

00:16.140 --> 00:18.059
- ♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:18.143 --> 00:20.145
♪ I GOT THE BEAT,
SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE WITH ME ♪

00:20.228 --> 00:21.688
♪ ME, ME, ME ♪

00:21.771 --> 00:23.690
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B ♪

00:23.773 --> 00:24.357
♪ BEE, BEE, BEE ♪

00:24.441 --> 00:28.027
♪ ♪

00:28.111 --> 00:31.281
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:31.364 --> 00:33.324
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B ♪

00:37.203 --> 00:38.121
[upbeat music]

00:38.204 --> 00:46.087
♪ ♪

00:46.171 --> 00:51.009
- [whistling]

00:51.092 --> 00:53.636
[chomping]

00:53.720 --> 00:55.138
[whistling]

00:57.974 --> 00:59.559
[metal jangling]

01:00.185 --> 01:01.519
[noisemaker blows]

01:01.603 --> 01:02.479
- SURPRISE!

01:02.562 --> 01:04.730
- [belches]

01:04.813 --> 01:07.233
- WELCOME BACK.

01:07.317 --> 01:10.737
CONGRATULATIONS
ON RUNNING ERRANDS.

01:13.198 --> 01:16.284
- [snarling]

01:16.367 --> 01:18.995
- WELL, THAT'S ONE WAY
OF SAYING THANK YOU, HAPPY.

01:19.078 --> 01:23.833
MOST PEOPLE LOVE
MY SURPRISE PARTIES.

01:27.086 --> 01:28.213
UHHHH.

01:28.296 --> 01:29.214
- SURPRISE!

01:29.297 --> 01:31.049
- AAAAAH!

01:31.132 --> 01:33.259
- SURPRISE!
- [screams]

01:33.343 --> 01:34.969
- SURPRISE!
- [shrieks]

01:35.053 --> 01:36.554
- SURPRISE!
- [screams]

01:36.638 --> 01:37.263
- SURPRISE!

01:37.347 --> 01:39.599
- HA HA!
I GET IT!

01:41.434 --> 01:44.979
- I KNOW I WOULD LOVE IT
IF SOMEONE WERE TO THROW ME ONE.

01:45.063 --> 01:46.397
squish!

01:46.481 --> 01:47.690
WHY, NO, FINGER.

01:47.774 --> 01:50.109
NO ONE EVER HAS THROWN ME
A SURPRISE PARTY.

01:50.193 --> 01:51.945
HMM, THAT IS
A VERY INTERESTING POINT

01:52.028 --> 01:53.696
THAT I NEVER THOUGHT OF
UNTIL RIGHT NOW.

01:53.780 --> 01:57.617
- [muttering]

01:57.700 --> 01:59.327
- OH, HAP,
DON'T YOU KNOW IT'S TACKY

01:59.410 --> 02:01.704
TO THROW YOURSELF
A SURPRISE PARTY?

02:01.788 --> 02:04.707
BESIDES, WITH SO MANY
LOVING FRIENDS, FAMILY,

02:04.791 --> 02:06.709
AND LOYAL PETS,

02:06.793 --> 02:11.798
I'M SURE SOMEONE
WILL SURPRISE ME SOON.

02:11.881 --> 02:13.591
splat!

02:13.675 --> 02:14.551
[noisemaker blows]

02:14.634 --> 02:17.637
- URGGHIII!

02:17.720 --> 02:19.556
[laughs]

02:19.639 --> 02:20.181
- OH, THAT'S NOT A SURPRISE.

02:20.265 --> 02:21.224
I SAW THAT COMING.

02:25.812 --> 02:29.732
[alarm clock ringing]

02:29.816 --> 02:31.943
[clanging]

02:32.026 --> 02:35.071
- [yawns]

02:36.447 --> 02:38.366
[groans]

02:39.659 --> 02:41.953
- GOOD MORNING, GENTLEMEN.

02:42.036 --> 02:44.330
BREAKFAST IS SERVED.

02:44.414 --> 02:45.415
both: HUH?

02:45.498 --> 02:46.916
- OH, THESE?

02:47.000 --> 02:50.378
IT'S JUST WE HAVE SUCH A SURPLUS
OF SURPRISE-PARTY CANDLES

02:50.461 --> 02:52.255
LYING AROUND THE HOUSE,
YOU KNOW,

02:52.338 --> 02:53.548
JUST WAITING
FOR A SURPRISE PARTY.

02:53.631 --> 02:57.927
I MEAN, NOTHING REALLY SHOUTS
"SURPRISE" LIKE CANDLES,

02:58.011 --> 03:00.263
AND NO ONE'S SHOUTING "SURPRISE"
RIGHT NOW,

03:00.346 --> 03:02.307
SO...

03:02.390 --> 03:04.183
HAPPY BREAKFAST.

03:04.267 --> 03:07.478
- IS SHE DOING THAT
"ART OF SUGGESTION" STUFF AGAIN.

03:07.562 --> 03:08.938
- [snarls]

03:09.022 --> 03:10.773
- I BEG YOUR PARDON.

03:10.857 --> 03:14.277
I GUESS A PERSON CAN'T EVEN MAKE
POLITE MORNING CONVERSATION

03:14.360 --> 03:16.070
ABOUT SURPRISE-PARTY CANDLES

03:16.154 --> 03:18.698
WITHOUT OTHER PEOPLE
PROJECTING THEIR OWN DESIRE

03:18.781 --> 03:20.158
TO THROW THEIR SISTER
A SURPRISE PARTY.

03:20.241 --> 03:23.953
UGH, THAT IS YOUR ISSUE
TO WORK THROUGH.

03:27.540 --> 03:28.666
WHAT?
WHERE DID THESE COME FROM?

03:28.750 --> 03:30.710
YOU DROPPED THESE.

03:30.793 --> 03:31.794
snap!

03:31.878 --> 03:33.922
snap!

03:40.136 --> 03:42.096
SURPRISE!

03:42.180 --> 03:44.515
DID YOU KNOW THAT SHREDDED PAPER
MAKES AN EXCELLENT

03:44.599 --> 03:47.936
ECO-FRIENDLY ALTERNATIVE
TO CONFETTI?

03:49.228 --> 03:50.188
snap!

03:50.271 --> 03:51.397
AAAGGGH.

03:54.525 --> 03:56.611
[mystical flute music]

03:56.694 --> 04:01.199
♪ ♪

04:01.282 --> 04:02.158
pop! pop!

04:02.241 --> 04:02.659
[noisemakers toot]

04:02.742 --> 04:04.994
poof!

04:05.078 --> 04:06.412
SO AS YOU CAN SEE IN THIS--

04:06.496 --> 04:07.664
THROW ME A SURPRISE PARTY--
PIE CHART,

04:07.747 --> 04:10.583
THE LAST QUARTER WAS--
I LOVE SURPRISE PARTIES--

04:10.667 --> 04:13.169
MORE SUCCESSFUL BY--
MAKE SURE IT'S A SURPRISE--

04:13.252 --> 04:15.171
A MARGIN OF--
I'M AVAILABLE SATURDAY--

04:15.254 --> 04:16.673
5%.

04:16.755 --> 04:18.966
RENT A PONY.

04:20.927 --> 04:22.011
OH, MY SEASONAL ALLERGIES.

04:22.095 --> 04:25.264
UH-UH-UH A--
SURPRISE PARTY.

04:25.348 --> 04:27.225
UH--A SURPRISE PARTY.

04:27.308 --> 04:28.810
A--TWO SURPRISE PARTIES.

04:28.893 --> 04:30.937
[squeaking]

04:33.356 --> 04:35.108
AHH.

04:35.191 --> 04:37.318
NOW, THAT'S THE ART
OF SUGGESTION.

04:39.737 --> 04:41.656
OH, HI, D--

04:41.739 --> 04:43.324
[gasps]

04:46.411 --> 04:50.790
THOSE LOOK UNMISTAKABLY LIKE
INVITATIONS TO A SURPRISE PARTY.

04:50.873 --> 04:52.709
I MEAN, WHAT ELSE COULD THEY BE.

04:52.792 --> 04:56.421
PHONE BILLS AND SUBPOENAS
CERTAINLY DON'T COME IN PINK.

04:59.132 --> 05:00.967
SETTLE, HIGGENBOTTOM.

05:01.050 --> 05:02.802
STILL INCONCLUSIVE.

05:02.885 --> 05:03.886
"SURPRISE!"

05:03.970 --> 05:07.056
"FOR ME?
AW."

05:07.140 --> 05:08.683
"SURPRISE!"

05:08.766 --> 05:10.268
"YOU GUYS."

05:10.351 --> 05:11.310
"SURPRISE!"

05:11.394 --> 05:12.270
"AW."

05:12.353 --> 05:13.855
"SURPRISE!"

05:13.938 --> 05:14.897
"AW"

05:14.981 --> 05:18.568
- [yapping]

05:18.651 --> 05:20.236
[laughter]

05:20.319 --> 05:21.070
- [high pitched]
YOU TOTALLY DID SOUND

05:21.154 --> 05:23.823
LIKE A POODLE, MAN.

05:23.906 --> 05:25.700
- OH, DON'T MIND ME.

05:25.783 --> 05:27.452
I JUST WANT TO LOOK AT...

05:27.535 --> 05:30.788
THAT BUILD-YOUR-OWN-THEREMIN KIT
I'VE BEEN SAVING FOR.

05:30.872 --> 05:31.914
- NO CAN DO, MR. SISTER.

05:31.998 --> 05:34.042
I JUST SOLD IT.

05:34.125 --> 05:36.002
- OH, REALLY?

05:36.085 --> 05:37.587
YOU "SOLD IT."

05:37.670 --> 05:39.338
I SEE.
HMM.

05:39.422 --> 05:42.008
I GUESS IT COMES
AS A "SURPRISE" TO ME

05:42.091 --> 05:45.053
THAT YOU SOLD IT TO SOMEONE
OTHER THAN MYSELF.

05:45.136 --> 05:46.846
I UNDERSTAND.

05:46.929 --> 05:48.056
"WINK."

05:48.139 --> 05:50.683
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

05:50.767 --> 05:52.935
BUT HE'S KIND OF GIVING
THE WHOLE GAME AWAY.

05:53.019 --> 05:55.271
WELL, KEEP IT UP, GUYS.

05:55.354 --> 05:57.106
F.Y.I., MY FAVORITE
BALLOON ANIMALS

05:57.190 --> 06:00.026
ARE SNAKES AND CATERPILLARS.

06:00.109 --> 06:02.695
I THINK IT'S WORKING.

06:02.779 --> 06:04.947
[giggles]

06:05.031 --> 06:06.449
[noisemaker blows]

06:09.327 --> 06:12.246
0.017-SECOND IMPROVEMENT.

06:12.330 --> 06:13.372
NICE!

06:13.456 --> 06:15.291
DON'T GET TOO COCKY,
HIGGENBOTTOM.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.668
YOU COULD STILL CHOKE
AT PARTY TIME.

06:17.752 --> 06:20.338
PIRATE BINGO WITH DARREN--
CANCELED.

06:20.421 --> 06:22.465
DOUBLES PING-PONG--
RESCHEDULED.

06:22.548 --> 06:24.467
THERE, NOW I AM COMPLETELY OPEN

06:24.550 --> 06:28.012
FOR A SURPRISE PARTY
ANY DAY THIS WEEK OR NEXT.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.806
ONE SLICE
OF LEMON ROSEMARY CAKE.

06:29.889 --> 06:31.474
HEAVY ON THE FROSTING, PLEASE.

06:31.557 --> 06:33.643
- SORRY, ALL SOLD OUT
OF LEMON ROSEMARY,

06:33.726 --> 06:37.355
BUT THERE'S PLENTY
OF WEEK-OLD BRAN MUFFINS LEFT.

06:38.439 --> 06:39.690
- SOLD OUT?

06:39.774 --> 06:42.276
thwack!

06:42.360 --> 06:46.197
EVERYONE KNOWS LEMON ROSEMARY
CAKE IS MY FAVORITE.

06:46.280 --> 06:47.323
splat!

06:47.406 --> 06:49.742
RED FLAG.

06:49.826 --> 06:52.328
THIS PARTY IS NOT HAPPENING
THIS WEEK OR NEXT.

06:52.411 --> 06:53.996
THIS PARTY IS HAPPENING...

06:54.080 --> 06:56.290
TODAY.

06:59.168 --> 07:00.169
squeak!

07:02.672 --> 07:05.091
HEY, BEN,
THAT'S VERY FANCY GLITTER.

07:05.174 --> 07:06.843
- YEP.

07:06.926 --> 07:07.844
OH, MOM WANTS YOU
TO RUN TO THE STORE

07:07.927 --> 07:09.679
AND PICK UP
SOME PEACOCK FEATHERS.

07:09.762 --> 07:11.639
IT'S A SPIRITUAL EMERGENCY.

07:11.722 --> 07:13.099
- AGAIN?

07:13.182 --> 07:14.058
OH!

07:14.142 --> 07:14.851
OH, OH, SURE.

07:14.934 --> 07:16.519
NO PROBLEM.

07:16.602 --> 07:20.648
I'M GOING TO
"FEATHERS ET CETERA" NOW.

07:20.731 --> 07:23.192
I'LL BE BACK
IN 25 MINUTES EXACTLY.

07:23.276 --> 07:25.611
AND I WILL KNOCK
BEFORE I COME IN

07:25.695 --> 07:27.029
SO YOU KNOW THAT I'M BACK.

07:27.113 --> 07:27.530
- OKAY.

07:31.284 --> 07:32.451
- "PEACOCK FEATHERS."

07:32.535 --> 07:34.203
"SPIRITUAL EMERGENCY."

07:34.287 --> 07:35.329
"MOM SAID."

07:35.413 --> 07:36.414
PLEASE.

07:36.497 --> 07:37.540
I HAPPEN TO KNOW
MOM'S DREAM CATCHERS

07:37.623 --> 07:40.793
ARE ALL MADE OUT OF OWL
AND GOOSE FEATHERS.

07:40.877 --> 07:43.379
THIS IS OBVIOUSLY AN EXCUSE
TO GET ME OUT OF THE HOUSE

07:43.462 --> 07:44.463
FOR THE SURPRISE.

07:44.547 --> 07:46.549
HUH, ROOKIES.
ADORABLE.

07:52.138 --> 07:53.389
sproing!

07:53.472 --> 07:56.517
GIVE ME SOMETHING SPECIAL,
SOMETHING GUEST-OF-HONOR-Y.

07:56.601 --> 07:56.684
poof!

08:01.147 --> 08:04.233
[shears clipping]

08:05.860 --> 08:08.613
PERFECT!

08:10.865 --> 08:11.949
pop!

08:12.033 --> 08:14.076
[gasps]

08:14.160 --> 08:20.917
[gasping]

08:21.000 --> 08:24.587
- [growling]

08:24.670 --> 08:27.423
- [gasping]

08:27.506 --> 08:30.760
GOT IT!
THAT'S THE ONE.

08:30.843 --> 08:32.010
[watch beeping]

08:32.094 --> 08:32.929
OOH, TIME TO GET BACK.

08:35.181 --> 08:36.265
smack!

08:39.769 --> 08:41.187
snap!

08:41.270 --> 08:41.770
[creaking]

08:41.854 --> 08:44.273
[gasps]

08:57.411 --> 08:59.247
[gasps]

08:59.330 --> 09:02.416
HELLO, MOTHER AND BEN.

09:02.500 --> 09:05.002
I HAVE RETURNED
WITH YOUR FEATHERS,

09:05.086 --> 09:06.545
AS REQUESTED.

09:09.423 --> 09:10.424
HMM.

09:10.508 --> 09:11.175
MAYBE I'M IN THE WRONG ROOM.

09:11.259 --> 09:14.345
OH, MY.
WHAT A SURPRISE.

09:14.428 --> 09:16.806
HUH.
WRONG ROOM AGAIN.

09:16.889 --> 09:20.559
ALL THIS FOR ME?

09:20.643 --> 09:24.355
UPSTAIRS--
MUCH MORE UNEXPECTED.

09:25.273 --> 09:26.774
YOU SHOULDN'T HAVE!

09:26.857 --> 09:28.234
I HAD NO IDEA!

09:28.317 --> 09:32.071
I'M SO SURPRISED!

09:32.154 --> 09:33.990
YOU GOT ME--

09:38.911 --> 09:39.829
WHAT?

09:39.912 --> 09:41.122
FOR ME?

09:41.205 --> 09:45.501
[wind howls]

09:45.584 --> 09:47.670
WELL...

09:47.753 --> 09:53.801
I GUESS THIS LACK OF A SURPRISE
IS...TECHNICALLY A SURPRISE.

09:53.884 --> 09:56.178
[chattering]

09:56.262 --> 09:59.140
[mournful violin music]

09:59.223 --> 10:01.517
[shattering sound]

10:03.311 --> 10:06.689
♪ ♪

10:06.772 --> 10:09.608
[vacuum whirring]

10:10.818 --> 10:14.155
♪ ♪

10:46.354 --> 10:49.106
- HERE WE SEE
SEVERAL SEA CUCUMBERS

10:49.190 --> 10:53.277
UNEXPECTEDLY FLOATING OUT
TO GREET ANOTHER SEA CUCUMBER.

10:53.361 --> 10:54.612
OOH, BOY.

10:54.695 --> 10:56.697
HE DIDN'T SEE THAT COMING.

10:56.781 --> 10:58.449
- [sobbing]

10:58.532 --> 10:59.408
thwack!

10:59.492 --> 11:00.326
[noisemaker blows]

11:00.409 --> 11:03.954
OH, THANKS, FING'.

11:04.038 --> 11:06.374
YOU'RE SUCH A GOOD FRIEND.

11:06.457 --> 11:09.919
THIS IS WHY WE'RE LIKE THIS.

11:20.888 --> 11:23.099
all: SURPRISE!

11:23.182 --> 11:24.475
- [screaming]

11:24.558 --> 11:27.269
[monkey-like shrieking]

11:27.353 --> 11:29.105
[gasping]

11:29.188 --> 11:31.065
OH!

11:31.148 --> 11:32.525
OH, I DON'T LIKE IT!

11:32.608 --> 11:33.818
OH, I DON'T LIKE IT!
I DON'T LIKE IT!

11:33.901 --> 11:35.111
I DON'T LIKE IT!
I DON'T LIKE IT!

11:35.194 --> 11:38.114
I DON'T LIKE IT!
IT'S SCARY.

11:38.197 --> 11:43.994
[electronic beeping]

11:46.372 --> 11:49.667
- 2 1/2 MINUTES LATE.

11:49.750 --> 11:52.878
2 1/2 MINUTES
AND 6.5 SECONDS LATE.

11:52.962 --> 11:55.297
OKAY.
DEEP BREATH.

11:55.381 --> 11:56.882
OOH.

11:56.966 --> 12:00.803
THERE ARE LOTS OF REASONS
FOR EXTREME TARDINESS:

12:00.886 --> 12:03.973
LONG LINE AT THE BANK,
TRAFFIC, LEGS WON'T START.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.808
EVERYTHING'S FINE.
EVERYTHING'S FINE.

12:05.891 --> 12:07.393
JUST FINE.

12:11.063 --> 12:14.150
HELLO, FBI, I'D LIKE TO REPORT
A DOGNAPPING.

12:14.233 --> 12:15.985
VICTIM IS BLUE
WITH A PARTIAL RIGHT EAR,

12:16.068 --> 12:19.738
ANSWERS TO "HAPPY,"
SMELLS LIKE BEANS.

12:21.157 --> 12:22.158
squish!

12:24.827 --> 12:25.953
NEVER MIND.

12:26.036 --> 12:27.663
VICTIM RECOVERED.

12:27.746 --> 12:28.581
beep!

12:28.664 --> 12:30.875
HAPPY, WHERE WERE YOU?

12:30.958 --> 12:31.917
AH!

12:32.001 --> 12:33.002
[kissing sounds]

12:35.588 --> 12:36.422
sproing!

12:36.505 --> 12:38.257
UGGH.
DUMPSTER DIVING AGAIN.

12:38.340 --> 12:39.425
BAD BOY!

12:39.508 --> 12:40.676
AH, GOOD BOY.

12:40.759 --> 12:42.678
[kissing sounds]

12:42.761 --> 12:45.014
DO YOU KNOW HOW WORRIED I WAS?

12:45.097 --> 12:47.266
I MEAN, WHAT IF YOU
WERE REALLY LOST?

12:47.349 --> 12:50.186
WHAT WOULD I DO?

12:50.269 --> 12:52.897
[crackling and buzzing]

12:52.980 --> 12:53.856
[gasps]

12:53.939 --> 12:54.940
THAT'S IT!

12:55.024 --> 12:56.275
I'M GETTING YOU
A DOGGY I.D. CHIP

12:56.358 --> 13:00.488
SO I'LL ALWAYS BE ABLE TO TRACK
YOUR EXACT WHEREABOUTS.

13:00.571 --> 13:01.530
- HUH?

13:01.614 --> 13:04.033
[muttering]

13:04.116 --> 13:05.367
- HEY.

13:05.451 --> 13:06.118
I'M THE BOSS, TOMATO SAUCE.

13:06.202 --> 13:08.370
COME ON.

13:10.915 --> 13:13.709
FREEDOM SCHMEEDOM, HAPPY.

13:13.792 --> 13:14.502
KNOWING YOUR SAFE
IS MORE IMPORTANT

13:14.585 --> 13:16.921
THAN YOUR CIVIL LIBERTIES.

13:17.004 --> 13:18.339
[scraping]

13:18.422 --> 13:20.049
REMEMBER, THERE'S A DELICIOUS
DOG BISCUIT

13:20.132 --> 13:21.759
WAITING FOR YOU AT THE END.

13:21.842 --> 13:23.886
CHIN UP, BOY.

13:23.969 --> 13:25.054
- [yaps]

13:28.307 --> 13:32.061
- A COVER STORY ON SIXTH-CENTURY
TURKISH TAPESTRIES?

13:32.144 --> 13:34.396
SCORE.

13:34.480 --> 13:36.857
[whirring and clanking]

13:36.941 --> 13:39.193
[buzzing and pulsing]

13:39.276 --> 13:43.989
[zapping]

13:44.073 --> 13:44.532
[heavy thuds]

13:44.615 --> 13:47.576
[sawing sounds]

13:47.660 --> 13:49.411
thwack! thwack! thwack!

13:49.495 --> 13:52.248
smash! smash! smash!

13:52.331 --> 13:53.832
[creaking]

13:57.294 --> 13:59.630
-<i> FINITO.</i>

13:59.713 --> 14:01.757
[ominous music]

14:01.840 --> 14:03.133
- [gasps]

14:04.969 --> 14:06.720
- NOW, WOULD YOU LIKE TO KNOW

14:06.804 --> 14:08.597
ABOUT THE RISKS
OF THE PROCEDURE?

14:08.681 --> 14:13.185
[whirring]

14:13.269 --> 14:14.436
- [whimpers]

14:14.520 --> 14:16.272
- DON'T WANT TO SPOIL
YOUR DINNER?

14:16.355 --> 14:19.650
HAPPY, YOU'VE REALLY MATURED
IN THE LAST FIVE MINUTES.

14:19.733 --> 14:21.735
I'M IMPRESSED.

14:24.780 --> 14:26.740
[crickets chirping]

14:27.491 --> 14:31.036
UGH, I'M STUFFED.

14:31.120 --> 14:32.955
- [gasps]
<i>SEA CUCUMBER COLONY</i>

14:33.038 --> 14:35.583
STARTS IN THREE MINUTES.

14:36.792 --> 14:37.626
MY PIE!

14:37.710 --> 14:39.795
I WAS GONNA GO BACK TO THAT.

14:43.549 --> 14:45.175
squish!

14:45.259 --> 14:46.885
[hissing]

14:46.969 --> 14:48.304
thwack!

14:48.387 --> 14:50.889
- YOU, SIR, ARE PURE CLASS.

14:50.973 --> 14:53.642
- SOMETHING FISHY'S GOING ON.

14:53.726 --> 14:55.603
WHAT'S YOUR GAME, DOG?

14:57.438 --> 14:58.856
- I BEG YOUR PARDON.

14:58.939 --> 15:01.358
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST ACCEPT
THAT MY YEARS OF TRAINING

15:01.442 --> 15:03.319
HAVE FINALLY PAID OFF
ALL AT ONCE?

15:03.402 --> 15:05.529
- BECAUSE IT'S HAPPY.

15:05.613 --> 15:07.072
- YOU KNOW, AN EX-CON
CAN'T GO STRAIGHT

15:07.156 --> 15:08.324
IF YOU DON'T LET HIM.

15:08.407 --> 15:09.408
I'M DISAPPOINTED IN--

15:09.491 --> 15:12.161
- [muttering]

15:12.244 --> 15:15.623
- WELL, THAT'S VERY BIG
OF YOU, HAPPY.

15:15.706 --> 15:17.791
NOT THAT HE DESERVES
YOUR BIGNESS.

15:17.875 --> 15:18.751
COME ON.

15:18.834 --> 15:20.711
LET'S LEAVE BEN
TO HIS CYNICISM.

15:20.794 --> 15:22.880
SEE HOW FAR IT GETS YOU, BEN.

15:22.963 --> 15:24.673
JUST SEE HOW FAR.

15:24.757 --> 15:26.216
[rumbling fart]

15:26.300 --> 15:27.217
- [sniffs]

15:27.301 --> 15:27.676
smack! smack!

15:27.760 --> 15:29.720
EUGH.

15:29.803 --> 15:32.014
- [mutters]

15:32.723 --> 15:36.143
- OH, CUCUMBER MELON.

15:39.980 --> 15:40.689
- MY SLIPPERS!

15:40.773 --> 15:44.193
OH, WHY, THANK YOU, HAPPY.

15:44.276 --> 15:47.196
YOU SEWED UP
ALL YOUR BITE MARKS.

15:47.279 --> 15:50.240
- RAAGH.

15:50.324 --> 15:54.703
- WHAT A...GOOD BOY.

15:54.787 --> 15:57.831
ALMOST TOO GOOD.

16:00.000 --> 16:01.710
SIT.

16:01.794 --> 16:03.087
ROLL OVER.

16:03.170 --> 16:04.046
BEG.

16:04.129 --> 16:05.172
PLAY DEAD.

16:05.255 --> 16:06.215
FIRST POSITION.

16:06.298 --> 16:08.008
SECOND, THIRD.
<i>RELEVE.</i>

16:08.092 --> 16:09.551
TRIPLE AXEL/DOUBLE TOE LOOP.

16:09.635 --> 16:11.136
NIXON.

16:11.220 --> 16:12.304
[gasps]

16:12.388 --> 16:13.972
HAPPY.

16:14.056 --> 16:15.432
WHAT IS YOUR MIDDLE NAME?

16:15.516 --> 16:16.141
- RAAGH RAAGH.

16:16.225 --> 16:18.268
- WALTER.
YES.

16:18.352 --> 16:21.438
UM...HOW MANY BACON-RELATED
PUBLICATIONS

16:21.522 --> 16:23.357
DO YOU SUBSCRIBE TO?

16:23.440 --> 16:24.358
- AGHH BLUGGH.

16:24.441 --> 16:25.567
- YES, INCLUDING BLOGS.

16:25.651 --> 16:26.318
- RUGGGH.

16:26.402 --> 16:28.320
- 12.
RIGHT AGAIN.

16:28.404 --> 16:29.571
ding!

16:29.655 --> 16:30.572
ONE LAST QUESTION.

16:30.656 --> 16:33.992
WHAT'S YOUR PIN CODE?

16:34.076 --> 16:36.328
- UGGH AAGH RAAGH NAAH.

16:36.412 --> 16:38.622
- [gasps]
THAT WAS A TRICK QUESTION.

16:38.706 --> 16:41.875
YOU WOULD NEVER TRUST ME
WITH THAT INFORMATION.

16:41.959 --> 16:44.837
WHO...ARE YOU?

16:44.920 --> 16:49.299
AND WHAT HAVE YOU DONE
WITH...MY HAPPY?

16:50.592 --> 16:52.845
JUST LOOK AT HIM!

16:52.928 --> 16:55.180
HE'S THE PICTURES OF HEALTH.

16:55.264 --> 16:56.598
- OH, REALLY, DOCTOR?

16:56.682 --> 16:59.393
HAPPY, WOULD YOU LIKE
A BOOSTER SHOT?

16:59.476 --> 17:01.687
- URGGH OH.

17:02.855 --> 17:05.107
- I MEAN, WHO DOES THAT?

17:05.190 --> 17:07.358
IT'S NOT NATURAL.

17:07.443 --> 17:08.318
- YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:08.402 --> 17:09.486
IT'S NOT THE NORMAL REACTION.

17:09.569 --> 17:11.655
LET'S HAVE A LOOKY LOU,
SHALL WE?

17:11.739 --> 17:14.074
[beeping]

17:14.157 --> 17:14.867
thwack!

17:14.950 --> 17:16.242
OH, THAT'S NOT GOOD.

17:16.326 --> 17:19.788
LOOKS LIKE I MIGHT HAVE PUT
THAT CHIP IN HIS BRAIN.

17:19.872 --> 17:22.374
IT REALLY SHOULD HAVE BEEN
BEHIND THE KNEE.

17:22.458 --> 17:24.417
AW, TRUFFLES.

17:26.170 --> 17:27.463
THERE IT IS.

17:27.546 --> 17:29.631
RIGHT IN HIS BAD-BEHAVIOR LOBE.

17:33.177 --> 17:35.012
thwap!

17:35.095 --> 17:37.139
- SO I GUESS WE BETTER
TAKE IT OUT.

17:37.222 --> 17:38.557
- UH, TAKE WHAT OUT?

17:39.516 --> 17:42.144
- THE CHIP!

17:42.227 --> 17:43.479
- RIGHT, RIGHT.

17:43.562 --> 17:44.813
WELL, THAT'S A NO-CAN-DO,
BUCKAROO.

17:44.897 --> 17:46.940
- WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

17:47.024 --> 17:49.318
- I CAN'T TAKE OUT THE CHIP.

17:49.401 --> 17:52.029
IF I DID, HOPPY HERE
COULD GO ON A RAMPAGE

17:52.112 --> 17:54.072
BECAUSE OF ALL OF HIS
REPRESSED BAD BEHAVIOR.

17:54.156 --> 17:58.994
- BUT...THIS IS NOT
MY HAPPY, DOCTOR.

17:59.077 --> 18:01.830
I WANT <i> MY</i> HAPPY BACK.

18:01.914 --> 18:05.876
- DON'T WE ALL
WANT OUR HAPPY BACK?

18:05.959 --> 18:07.252
LOOK, ON THE BRIGHT SIDE,
HE'S SO OBEDIENT NOW,

18:07.336 --> 18:10.380
YOU CAN TRAIN HIM TO BE
WHATEVER YOU WANT HIM TO BE,

18:10.464 --> 18:12.508
LIKE A BOBCAT OR A TOASTER.

18:12.591 --> 18:15.177
- WHAT?

18:15.260 --> 18:16.553
HAPPY?

18:16.637 --> 18:19.473
UNSNAP YOUR LEASH.

18:19.556 --> 18:21.183
YOU'RE GOING
TO DISOBEDIENCE SCHOOL.

18:23.769 --> 18:25.646
OKAY, BOY.

18:25.729 --> 18:27.648
WE GOT A LOT OF WORK TO DO.

18:30.943 --> 18:32.194
DIG, DIG, DIG!
DIG, DIG, DIG!

18:32.277 --> 18:34.822
OOH, IT FEELS SO GOOD
TO BE BAD.

18:35.781 --> 18:37.032
COME ON, BOY.

18:41.286 --> 18:42.579
- ARRGGH.

18:42.663 --> 18:44.122
- [sighs]
YES, HAPPY.

18:44.206 --> 18:45.624
VERY PRETTY.

18:47.501 --> 18:48.418
COME ON, BOY.

18:48.502 --> 18:49.545
YOUR TURN.

18:54.508 --> 18:54.925
- NO, NO.

18:55.008 --> 18:56.593
PEE ON IT.

18:56.677 --> 18:57.219
AAGH!
PEE!

19:00.848 --> 19:04.726
AH, WHAT A JUICY, DELICIOUS
STEAK I'M WALKING AWAY FROM

19:04.810 --> 19:06.270
AND NOT EVEN LOOKING AT.

19:06.353 --> 19:08.689
- [sniffing]

19:08.772 --> 19:11.525
- [gasps]
FINALLY.

19:11.608 --> 19:13.110
HAPPY KRYPTONITE.

19:14.403 --> 19:15.779
blop!

19:15.863 --> 19:17.406
[pattering]

19:17.489 --> 19:20.450
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
TO MAKE YOU NOT BEHAVE?

19:24.621 --> 19:28.292
[laughs]

19:29.960 --> 19:30.836
- URGGGH.

19:30.919 --> 19:32.421
- OH, HAPPY.

19:32.504 --> 19:34.590
WHY SO SOULLESS?

19:34.673 --> 19:36.925
- WHAT?
WHAT'S GOING ON?

19:37.718 --> 19:39.970
[voices clamoring]

19:52.566 --> 19:56.695
- [whimpering]

19:56.778 --> 19:58.697
- DON'T KNOW WHAT
CAME OVER YOU, HUH?

19:58.780 --> 20:01.783
INTERESTING.

20:01.867 --> 20:03.952
VERY INTERESTING.

20:07.456 --> 20:10.792
BEN, HOW DO YOU FEEL
ABOUT BEING DOG BAIT?

20:10.876 --> 20:11.627
- AGAIN?

20:11.710 --> 20:15.255
HOW MUCH?

20:15.339 --> 20:16.757
- THIS DOG MEANS
THE WORLD TO ME.

20:16.840 --> 20:18.675
ALL OF MY BEE BUCKS.

20:18.759 --> 20:20.260
- [gasps]

20:20.344 --> 20:23.263
I CAN GET A NEW TRAMPOLINE!

20:23.347 --> 20:27.184
- TRAMPOLINE AND A SHOE BUFFER,
TO BE EXACT.

20:29.227 --> 20:30.979
[knocking at door]

20:31.063 --> 20:32.314
OH, HAPPY.

20:32.397 --> 20:34.524
WOULD YOU MIND GETTING THAT?

20:34.608 --> 20:36.485
- ARRGGH.

20:38.528 --> 20:42.574
[dramatic music]

20:42.658 --> 20:44.326
[chattering]

20:44.409 --> 20:45.661
- BINGO.

20:45.744 --> 20:46.703
[chattering]

20:46.787 --> 20:47.412
pop!

20:47.496 --> 20:49.957
[steam whistle sound]

20:50.040 --> 20:50.916
- BACON!

20:50.999 --> 20:53.126
- [growling]

20:53.210 --> 20:55.295
[all moaning]

20:55.379 --> 20:57.631
- [howls]

20:57.714 --> 20:59.424
[cat yowling]

20:59.508 --> 21:00.342
- YES!

21:00.425 --> 21:02.094
IT'S WORKING!

21:02.177 --> 21:05.681
- [meows]

21:05.764 --> 21:07.808
[cheeks flapping]

21:09.685 --> 21:10.769
- [snarling]

21:10.852 --> 21:13.105
- [screams]

21:13.188 --> 21:16.233
- [snarling]

21:18.527 --> 21:21.113
- JUST CLOSE YOUR EYES AND THINK
OF YOUR NEW TRAMPOLINE.

21:21.196 --> 21:24.616
- BUT I CAN'T FEEL MY LEGS.

21:24.700 --> 21:25.283
- [snarling]

21:25.367 --> 21:30.247
- [yowling and hissing]

21:30.330 --> 21:32.499
- MY ALLERGIES!

21:33.709 --> 21:35.293
[all gasp]

21:37.421 --> 21:39.339
- [snarling]

21:43.593 --> 21:45.137
[growls]

21:49.641 --> 21:52.728
[whirring]

21:52.811 --> 21:54.021
smash!

21:55.147 --> 21:57.566
[sirens wail]

22:00.360 --> 22:02.279
- [sobbing]

22:02.362 --> 22:02.696
- [snarling]

22:02.779 --> 22:03.780
- HAPPY!

22:03.864 --> 22:08.201
- [growling]

22:08.285 --> 22:09.453
- IT'S OKAY.

22:09.536 --> 22:10.412
I'VE BEEN MEANING
TO CHANGE THE SHEETS.

22:11.830 --> 22:13.707
NO BIGGIE.

22:13.790 --> 22:15.083
I CAN JUST BUILD A NEW WALL.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.961
- [laughs]

22:18.045 --> 22:19.880
zap!

22:19.963 --> 22:20.922
- AWW.

22:21.006 --> 22:23.133
WHO'S A GOOD BOY?

22:23.216 --> 22:26.428
- [yelping]

22:26.511 --> 22:29.097
[whimpers]

22:29.181 --> 22:30.098
- WHEE!

22:30.182 --> 22:31.099
OW.

22:31.183 --> 22:32.267
WHEE!

22:32.350 --> 22:35.771
OW.

